                  <p><strong><em>Write a code to print Fibonacci series</em></strong></p>

<p><strong>Solution</strong></p>

<p>#!/usr/bin/python<br>
# Program to display the Fibonacci sequence up to nth term where n is provided by the user<br>
# take input from the user<br>
nterms = int(input("How many terms? "))<br>
# first two terms<br>
n1 = 0<br>
n2 = 1<br>
count = 2<br>
# check if the number of terms is valid<br>
if nterms &lt;= 0:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; print("Plese enter a positive integer")<br>
elif nterms == 1:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; print("Fibonacci sequence:")<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; print(n1)<br>
else:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; print ("Fibonacci sequence:")<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; print (n1,",",n2,end=" ,")<br>
while count &lt; nterms:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; nth = n1 + n2<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; if count !=(nterms-1):<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; print(nth,end=" ,")# update values<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; else:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; print (nth)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; n1 = n2<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; n2 = nth<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; count += 1</p>

